      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(otel): set logBodies=true in default content capture policy",
        "body": "Closes #95633\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nOTLP log bodies were empty by default. `NO_CONTENT_CAPTURE` (used when no explicit OTel config is provided) set `logBodies: false`. Additionally, the explicit config path hardcoded `logBodies: false`, ignoring the user's setting.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nTwo fixes:\n1. `NO_CONTENT_CAPTURE.logBodies: false → true` — users without explicit config get log bodies\n2. Explicit config path: `logBodies: false → config.logBodies === true` — respects user's explicit `logBodies` setting\n\n## Evidence\n\nThe `shouldCaptureOtelLogBody` function is internal (not exported), so the evidence replicates the exact production logic:\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx evidence-test.ts\n\nTest 1: No OTel config → shouldCaptureOtelLogBody = true  (after fix, was false)\nTest 2: { enabled: true } without logBodies → false (intentional backward compat)\nTest 3: { enabled: true, logBodies: true } → true (user setting now respected)\nTest 4: captureContent = true → true (unchanged)\n```",
        "branch": "fix/issue-95633-otlp-log-body",
